						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab lying to the east of the tank at Chauḷikēṟī.</p>						

						<p>Harihara II, 1397 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record registers a gift of land made in the presence of god Vināyaka of Kellaṁgeṟe, probably by <hi rend="bold">Śaṅkaradēvavoḍeya</hi> who was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya,</hi> for feeding Brāhmaṇas and probably also for worship and offerings to others deities. It also refers to a <hi rend="italic">basadi.</hi> Some of the gift lands appear to have been situated in the village Beḷugoṇḍa of Nālvattu-nāḍu. Bārahakanyāpura is mentioned.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 132[0], Īśvara, Āshāḍha śu. [3, Thursday]</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1397 A.D., June 28.</hi> The Śaka year was current.</p>						

						</summary>
